### API Testing File for Housekeepr
### Use this with REST Client extension in VS Code or PhpStorm HTTP Client

@baseUrl = http://localhost:8000/api
@token = YOUR_TOKEN_HERE

### 1. Login to get token
POST {{baseUrl}}/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "admin@example.com",
  "password": "password"
}

### 2. Get current user info
GET {{baseUrl}}/user
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 3. Get all bookings (owner)
GET {{baseUrl}}/bookings
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 4. Create a booking
POST {{baseUrl}}/bookings
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "room_id": 1,
  "check_in_datetime": "2025-12-10 14:00:00",
  "notes": "VIP guest"
}

### 5. Get specific booking
GET {{baseUrl}}/bookings/1
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 6. Update booking
PUT {{baseUrl}}/bookings/1
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "check_in_datetime": "2025-12-10 15:00:00",
  "notes": "Updated time"
}

### 7. Get all cleaning tasks
GET {{baseUrl}}/cleaning-tasks
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 8. Get specific cleaning task
GET {{baseUrl}}/cleaning-tasks/1
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 9. Start a cleaning task (cleaner only)
POST {{baseUrl}}/cleaning-tasks/1/start
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 10. Stop a cleaning task (cleaner only)
POST {{baseUrl}}/cleaning-tasks/1/stop
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 11. Complete a cleaning task (cleaner only)
POST {{baseUrl}}/cleaning-tasks/1/complete
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 12. Delete booking
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/bookings/1
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 13. Logout
POST {{baseUrl}}/logout
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

